channel.title: Stat Icons
channel.description:
Whilst ripping the skill icon images from my 459 cache I found these 2 images in the same list (a spade and a rat)
[URL=http://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/94/ratje.png/][IMG]http://img94.imageshack.us/img94/2283/ratje.png[/img][/URL] [URL=http://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/4/spadee.png/][IMG]http://img4.imageshack.us/img4/405/spadee.png[/img][/URL]
I'm just curious as to what they are for and why Jagex added them to the staticons libary? Are they skill icons that were scrapped or what?
Also, there are like 12 empty spaces, maybe they plan on releasing 12 new skills (like 9 now).

item.description:
@Rodgerwilco wrote:

Jagex… over the years have left quite a few things that were useless in the client. Look in the 458 cache and 460… (or the closest cache you can get) I am sure you can find something in each cache / client that is useless.

I was thinking the spade would be for clue scrolls but I doubt it (I am not too sure about the timings so yea a guess)

item.description:
@The_Outsider wrote:

Rodgerwilco:

As in stat icons… just the icons alone? or does it contain the icons for the skill “guide” (clicking on the skill) as well…

There’s a file called staticons and inside that are the skill icons (99/99 or whatever) for attack, strength, defence all the way down to farming and then there are these two icons at the bottom.
